  "prompt": "How do I book a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Uber does not support booking round trips as a single ride. Each trip you take with Uber is considered a separate ride. If you need to return to your original location, you will need to book a new ride for the return journey.\n\nHowever, you can make the process smoother by:\n\n1. **Booking a Ride:** Use the Uber app to book a ride to your destination.\n2. **Ending the Ride:** Once you reach your destination, end the ride.\n3. **Rebooking:** When you are ready to return, open the Uber app and book a new ride back to your original location.\n\nAlternatively, if you need the driver to wait for you at a stop and then continue the trip, you can use the \"Add a Stop\" feature in the Uber app. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. **Open the Uber App:** Enter your destination.\n2. **Add a Stop:** Once you have entered your destination, swipe up or tap on the plus sign (+) to add a stop.\n3. **Enter the Stop Location:** Input the location where you need to stop. You can add up to two extra stops.\n4. **Adjust Timing:** Communicate with your driver about the duration of the stop.\n\nKeep in mind that adding stops may increase the fare and that drivers may not be able to wait for extended periods.\n\nAlways check the latest updates on the Uber app or website, as features and policies may change over time.",
